FBIS4-18792 "drweu069_p_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 GREECE Defense Minister Visits U.S. Bases in Crete Defense Minister Visits U.S. Bases in Crete NC1004184794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1700 GMT 10 Apr 94 NC1004184794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis today visited the installations of the U.S. military base in Gournes, Crete. The bases will be turned over to the Greek Government tomorrow after 30 years of U.S. Administration. Arsenis said the bases will not be used for military purposes and added that the committee that has been established for this purpose will examine ways of utilizing the bases' buildings and territory.
